针对封锁，[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]]评论到“在名单中加入GitHub……是最脑残的决定之一”，并预言GitHub在信息技术领域的重要性会使封禁行为引发抗议。<!--They also called it embarrassing in the context of [[总理|Prime Minister]] [[纳伦德拉·莫迪|Narendra Modi]]'s {{tsl|en|Make in India||Make in India}} campaign to promote India as a destination for [[信息技术|information technology]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Russell|first1=Jon|title=India’s Government Asks ISPs To Block GitHub, Vimeo And 30 Other Websites (Updated)|url=http://techcrunch.com/2014/12/31/indian-government-censorsht/|website=TechCrunch|accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref> Prasanth Sugathan of the Software Freedom and Law Center called the blocks short-sighted, saying that "If you block one website, terrorists can always use another one... Such a move only inconveniences the daily users..." -->Twitter用户通过“#GOIblocks”标签进行抗议，并引用[[纳伦德拉·莫迪|纳伦德拉·莫迪]]在2012年发表的信息来谴责网络封锁。<ref name=Arora-TOI>{{cite web|last1=Arora|first1=Kim|title=Government blocks 32 websites to check ISIS propaganda|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/Government-blocks-32-websites-to-check-ISIS-propaganda/articleshow/45712815.cms?|website=The Times of India - Tech|accessdate=2015-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150104134659/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/tech-news/Government-blocks-32-websites-to-check-ISIS-propaganda/articleshow/45712815.cms|archive-date=2015-01-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>印度[[匿名者|匿名者]]多次向政府发出威胁，但并未采取实际行动。<ref name=Sharma-TOI/>

== 土耳其 ==
[[File:October_9,_2016_GitHub_Turkey_block.jpg|thumb]]
2016年10月8日，在土耳其黑客组织{{le|RedHack|RedHack}}声称入侵土耳其能源部长、[[埃尔多安|埃尔多安]]女婿[[貝拉特·阿爾巴伊拉克|阿尔巴伊拉克]]之后，{{le|土耳其信息与通信技术署|Information and Communication Technologies Authority}}命令互联网服务供应商封锁几个[[檔案分享|檔案分享]]网站，包括[[Dropbox|Dropbox]]、[[OneDrive|Microsoft OneDrive]]、[[Google雲端硬碟|Google Drive]]<ref name=ref01>{{cite web|title=Dropbox, Google Drive and Microsoft OneDrive cloud services blocked in Turkey following leaks|url=https://turkeyblocks.org/2016/10/08/google-drive-dropbox-blocked-in-turkey/|website=Turkey Blocks|accessdate=2016-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161209235232/https://turkeyblocks.org/2016/10/08/google-drive-dropbox-blocked-in-turkey/|archive-date=2016-12-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>。觀測網路審查情況的[[Turkey_Blocks|Turkey Blocks]]注意到GitHub於次日上午被封鎖，並且相關的封鎖令被信息与通信技术署逐步發佈出來<ref name=ref01/>。封鎖導致依賴GitHub的軟體（例如[[Font_Awesome|Font Awesome]]、{{tsl|en|Homebrew||Homebrew}}等）無法正常運行。Startup Istanbul活動的參與者也表達了對基礎設施可用性的不滿。在土耳其，#GitHub[[主題標籤|標籤]]成為了Twitter的熱門標籤之一。按照[[The_Daily_Dot|The Daily Dot]]的說法，RedHack組織蓄意通過多種服務來傳播郵件內容，期待土耳其政府將其封鎖，以造成[[史翠珊效應|史翠珊效應]]。18小時後GitHub被解封<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sozeri|first1=Efe Kerem|title=How hacktivist group RedHack gamed Turkey’s censorship regime|url=http://www.dailydot.com/layer8/redhack-gamed-turkey-censorship/|website=Daily Dot|accessdate=2016-10-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013074044/http://www.dailydot.com/layer8/redhack-gamed-turkey-censorship/|archive-date=2016-10-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 美国 ==
2019年5月起，美国的出口管理条例开始对开源代码进行管制<ref>{{Cite web |url = http://news.mydrivers.com/1/627/627904.htm |title = Github更新用户协议 开源代码也要受美国出口管制 |author = 宪瑞 |date = 2019-05-21 |publisher = 快科技 |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2019-08-01 |archive-date = 2019-05-23 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190523185254/http://news.mydrivers.com/1/627/627904.htm |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

此時开始对[[伊朗|伊朗]]、[[叙利亚|叙利亚]]和克里米亚的私人repo和付费账户实施限制<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/JB4TyNRSMVJ5I39rDDBWeg |title = 美国对外实行制裁，致多个地区 GitHub 账号使用受限！ |author = GitHubDaily |date = 2019-07-26 |publisher = GitHubDaily |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2019-08-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190801035629/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/JB4TyNRSMVJ5I39rDDBWeg |archive-date = 2019-08-01 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ykXvqYJmic7to6vXkkQTng |title = GitHub CEO 正式回应账号访问受限事件！ |author = GitHubDaily |date = 2019-07-29 |publisher = GitHubDaily |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2019-08-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190801035633/https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ykXvqYJmic7to6vXkkQTng |archive-date = 2019-08-01 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.leiphone.com/news/201907/VYfal74uBwvwixdF.html |title = 令人心寒的不是 Github 突然断供，而是 CEO 对此表示无能为力 |author = 黄善清 |date = 2019-07-29 |publisher = 雷锋网 |language = zh-cn |accessdate = 2019-08-01 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190801035633/https://www.leiphone.com/news/201907/VYfal74uBwvwixdF.html |archive-date = 2019-08-01 |dead-url = no }}</ref>，2020年4月起一個名為Aurelia的軟體代碼被GitHub封鎖引起較大紛爭，其理由為參與的兩個志願者為伊朗人，引起該程式諸多志願者不滿並於硅谷的「 黑客新闻 」论坛大舉批判，後續GitHub改變作法重新啟動Aurelia頁面但封鎖兩個伊朗人帳號，之前並發生過一名為Hamed Saeed的開發者已經移民[[芬蘭|芬蘭]]多年但祖籍為伊朗而被封鎖的事件。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.leiphone.com/news/202003/AyU4SvQ694SpVs1b.html |title=雷鋒站-GitHub是开源，最终也是政治 |access-date=2020-04-10 |archive-date=2020-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201213213457/https://www.leiphone.com/news/202003/AyU4SvQ694SpVs1b.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>此事件引發一個後續討論，美國訂定的制裁他國法案僅限於不讓特定外國人使用美國技術，然而GitHub上的技術是各國志願者撰寫並無償分享，並非美國購買有版權的所有物，<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://github.com/mohebifar/made-in-iran |title=mohebifar /made-in-iran |access-date=2020-04-10 |archive-date=2020-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201213213501/https://github.com/mohebifar/made-in-iran |dead-url=no }}</ref>其中也包含[[伊朗|伊朗]]程式員也就是其實有伊朗的技術，美國無權拿不屬於自己的東西制裁別人甚至「拿伊朗的技術制裁伊朗」。GitHub最后在爭議下覺得有所理虧而改變作法，被封禁的用户可以下載回自己的作品，但依然不能在社区里查看代码。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.chainnews.com/zh-hant/articles/293428053482.htm |title=GitHub惹衆怒，CEO 親自道歉 |access-date=2020-04-10 |archive-date=2020-09-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200903050336/https://www.chainnews.com/zh-hant/articles/293428053482.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

